                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/90.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="149" xml:id="d1575fn149">Communicated to the German Ambassador February
                        16, 1914.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have interviewed Villa. Assure German Ambassador every protection will be given
                    German subjects at Torreon. Report by letter to-morrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
